EXCEL with VBAs

Add Developer Menu Option

- From Customize the Ribbon, select 'Developer'

Add Macro Menu Option

- To add Macros section:
  Select 'New Tab'
  Create name: 'NOLP Macros' (or whatever)
  While selecting newly created tab, (if this hasn't been done automatically) then press 'New Group' button and type name

  From 'Choose commands from:' section, select 'Macros'
  -  From Choose commands from:' side, select macro to add.
  - From 'Customize the Ribbon' section, select 'Main Tabs' and select new tab and new group. 
  - Press the middle button 'Add >>' to add macro to group (or any other command to any other group)

VBA Window

  Add RegEx:
  - 'Tools' -> 'References' -> Check 'Microsoft VBAScript Regular Expressions 5' and select 'Ok' button
  
  Add Debug Menu (contains 'Step Into' button)
  - Right click Menu bar and select 'Debug'

Show PERSONAL Worksheet
  - 'View' -> 'Unhide' (from 'Window' section) -> 'PERSONAL' -> press 'Ok'
